  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (fidelity gap variant)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CFD model employs a single-phase Newtonian blood surrogate and explicitly excludes non-Newtonian shear-thinning rheology; the impact of this exclusion on hemolysis index predictions was studied informally during development but no formal sensitivity analysis or fidelity trade study was documented or linked.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/cou1-hemolysis-requirement",
